widening casting is implicit
narrowing casting is explicit

the java compiler does not attempt to evaluate the value, in a variable, when it's used in a calculation, 
so it doesn't know if the value would fit, and throws error if narrow casting implicitly 
  ex 
    int minByte = Byte.MIN_VALUE;
    byte var = (minByte / 2); // error 

if calculation includes literal values, java compiler can figure out the end result at compile time, and whether 
it fits into the ariable, and won't throw an error if it does, a little confused about this behaviour, so just cast manually
  ex 
    byte var = (-128) / 2;

casting 
  byte minValue = (byte) Byte.MIN_VALUE; // int casted to byte


